Gall (
Figs 18–19
). Swelling, occurring on both unfolded young leaves and base of midrib, 1.8–2.5 mm long (n = 10 ). Galls located at the base of a leaf midrib are usually yellowish and single; galls on unopened young leaves are green and in clusters of 1–3 , multilocular. The two gall morphotypes can be found in the same month.
